description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you put patients first? &lt;br /&gt;Are you proud to be a Operating Department Practitioner?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If so then apply to come and work with us and become a member of our valued team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Chelsea and Westminster NHS Trust are recruiting Operating Department Practitioners to work in Main Theatres, Labour Ward, Recovery, Anaesthetics and Scrub.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Chelsea and Westminster Hospital NHS Foundation Trust aims to be a hospital of choice for patients and an employer of choice for staff. In order to improve all aspects of the patient experience, we rely upon having a highly skilled, motivated, diverse, productive and patient focused workforce. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In the latest annual national staff survey Chelsea and Westminster achieved the best score for an acute hospital trust nationally.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Why not work for a top acute trust committed to flexible working and diversity in employment?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Whilst covering a shift, you will provide professional leadership to staff and work in close collaboration and co-operation with other health care professionals. You will also be responsible for leading and managing staff and leading areas of service improvement as delegated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As well as competitive pay rates, you’ll be eligible for many benefits of working as a permanent member of staff , including:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• The chance to gain experience within a variety of departments&lt;br /&gt;• NHS Pension Scheme &lt;br /&gt;• NHS badge entitling you to discounts &lt;br /&gt;• Unsocial hours enhancements (where applicable)&lt;br /&gt;• Weekly pay&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We require individuals who are enthusiastic, well organised with a positive attitude towards flexibility and change. You will also need considerable post registration experience and have excellent communication skills.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are a committed, motivated reliable trained nurse who would enjoy the flexibility that ad hoc work brings, as well as the opportunity to experience different clinical settings working in this busy, diverse hospital this may be the job for you!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
